article.description: Markis McDuffie had 24 points including three 3-pointers in the final six minutes as Wichita State held on to defeat Appalachian State 82-76 at the Charleston Classic on Friday.
article.headline: Wichita State defeats Appalachian State 82-76
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Markis McDuffie had 24 points including three 3-pointers in the final six minutes as Wichita State held on to defeat Appalachian State 82-76 at the Charleston Classic on Friday. The Shockers (2-2) held a 10-point lead in the second half of their opener here against Davidson before falling 57-53. But this time, they prevailed after Appalachian State wiped away a seven-point deficit and led 66-61 with 6:18 remaining. That's when Wichita State finished with a flourish, outscoring the Mountaineers (1-3) 21-10 the rest of the way. Wichita State will face Alabama in the fifth-place game Sunday. Justin Forrest had 28 points for Appalachian State, who'll play Ball State on Sunday for seventh in the eight-team tournament.
